foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: Due to administrative error one FLRA request closed in FY '07 was counted as pending in the Agency's FY '07 Annual Report.

foia:ProcessedResponseTimeSection.foia:FootnoteText: Note: Since the agency generally responds to requests on a timely basis without the need to deal with FOIA backlog, it does not prioritize the processing of requests based on a multi-track processing system where requests are placed in either a simple or complex track based on complexity. A requester who has an urgent need for records may request expedited processing.

foia:InformationGrantedResponseTimeSecti.foia:FootnoteText: Note: As indicated earlier (see VII.A.) the FLRA does not distinguish between "simple" and "complex" requests, it processes all requests on a first-in/first-out basis. A requester who has an urgent need for records may request expedited processing.

foia:SimpleResponseTimeIncrementsSection.foia:FootnoteText: Note: As indicated earlier (see VII.A.) the FLRA does not distinguish between "simple" and "complex" requests, the information reflected in the table above accounts for all types of FOIA requests received by the agency.

foia:ExpeditedResponseTimeIncrementsSect.foia:FootnoteText: The agency had no perfected expedited processing requests.

foia:PendingPerfectedRequestsSection.foia:FootnoteText: As noted earlier, since the agency does not use a multi-track system to process requests, the information reflected in the table above accounts for all types of FOIA requests received by the agency.

foia:ExpeditedProcessingSection.foia:FootnoteText: The agency adjudicated no expedited processing requests during FY '08.

foia:BacklogSection.foia:FootnoteText: Since the close of the FY 2008 reporting period, the 10 backlogged requests have been closed.

foia:BackloggedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: Starting with the Annual Report for Fiscal Year 2009, Department of Justice guidance indicated agencies were to provide the number of backlogged requests as of the end of the fiscal year from the previous Annual Report and the number of backlogged requests as of the end of the fiscal year from the current Annual Report. See http://www.justice.gov/oip/foiapost/guidance-annualreport-052008.pdf. Based on this guidance, the agencys FY 2008 Annual Report did include the above referenced comparison data.
